.TH DSGBase 1 "June 2025" "v1.0" "User Binary Tool Manual"
.SH NAME
DSGBase \- convert and query user data in JSON and binary formats
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B DSGBase
[\fB-b\fR \fIFILE\fR] [\fB-f\fR \fIFILE\fR] [\fB-i\fR \fIID\fR] [\fB-n\fR \fINAME\fR] [\fB-s\fR \fISURNAME\fR] [\fB-r\fR \fIREGION\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B DSGBase
is a command-line tool for managing user data from JSON files. It can convert a JSON file to a binary format or search users by name, surname, ID, or region from a binary dataset.

The JSON input is expected to use the following keys for user objects:
.IP \[bu] 2
\fBsaxeli\fR – First name
.IP \[bu]
\fBgvari\fR – Surname
.IP \[bu]
\fBpiadi\fR – User ID (string form of integer)
.IP \[bu]
\fBraioni\fR – Region

The binary output is written to \fBoutput.bin\fR by default.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -b " " \fIFILE\fR
Convert the JSON file \fIFILE\fR to binary format. Output will be saved as \fBoutput.bin\fR. This flag is mutually exclusive with other flags.

.TP
.BR -f " " \fIFILE\fR
Load binary user data from \fIFILE\fR. Required before any search operation.

.TP
.BR -i " " \fIID\fR
Search for a user by integer ID.

.TP
.BR -n " " \fINAME\fR
Search for users by name (first name / saxeli).

.TP
.BR -s " " \fISURNAME\fR
Search for users by surname (gvari).

.TP
.BR -r " " \fIREGION\fR
Search for users by region (raioni).

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Convert JSON to binary:
.B
userbin -b users.json

.TP
Load binary file and search by ID:
.B
userbin -f output.bin -i 101

.TP
Load and search by name and region:
.B
userbin -f output.bin -n Giorgi -r Tbilisi

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns 0 on success, non-zero on failure. Error messages are printed to stderr.

.SH FILES
.TP
.B output.bin
The default output file for binary data after conversion.

.SH DEPENDENCIES
Requires the following libraries:
.IP \[bu] 2
libcjson
.IP \[bu]
uthash

.SH BUGS
Does not support searching by partial name or case-insensitive matches. No support for combining multiple search terms (e.g., name and surname together).

